<br>
-It's my personal opinion that Mastery Staves don't work on 61+ pets because of lack of coding, not by intention of designers.<br>
<br>
-Level 61-65 and epic pets have exactly one item in the entire game that can focus them.  That item is extremely rare and flat out not accessable to most mages.<br>
<br>
-New &quot;pet focus items&quot; don't HAVE TO focus exactly the same as mastery staves or Gloves of dark summoning.  They could focus different effects, like more DEX for proc rate, or higher resists, or more HP, or give all pets higher HP regen etc.  Be creative Sony.<br>
<br>
-Epic quest requires the loss of 5 focus items, 2 of which are not easy to come by at all, and one that never happens because you use the crown for epic and not for staff.  So getting epic makes your other pets WEAKER.<br>
<br>
-Having epic pet outperformed in some cases by PoP pets would be my more swallowable for me, if I could at least focus my new PoP pets with my hard earned Orb of Mastery.<br>
<br>
-If designers are worried about making epic pets too good, you can do other things at the same time to fix it.  Like nerf epic HP by 15%, then make the orb focus all pet HP by 15%.  So the epic does not become stronger, but the orb will still focus all pets.  Ideas like that could easily work for balance.<br>
<br>
-EQ Designers could also make the amount of focus dependant on the level of the pet.  Like increase all pet resists (pet level)/2 or something.  So PoP pets get 30 to all resists, but a level 44 pet would get 22.  Or perhaps Raise pet HP (pet level)*8.<br>
<br>
Anybody agree with this?  If yes let's get vocal and start a petition.<br>
<br>
==============================================<br>
EDIT: I changed the title from Petition, to discussion.  Since there was not a strong following in it's current form, but a strong feeling that this post was on the right track.<br>
