<br>
A quest of that magnitude shouldn't become obsolete and should have a lasting (Perhaps not profound, but usable) effect on your character for the LIFE of it.<br>
<br>
It wasn't called the &quot;Epic just for now&quot; quest.. it was intended at the time to be the greatest achievement ever for each class.<br>
<br>
The fact that it's been backpacked by so many end game people is somewhat sad.<br>
<br>
Here's another example in case you don't understand.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Tradeskills:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
These are old and outdated things. PRE-Kunark even in their antiquity. Why should they be viable still? Why do they bother coming up with new recipes for these old world skills?<br>
<br>
Oh, that's right.. because people spent <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A LOT OF TIME</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> on them.<br>
<br>
That investment should never be something that's thrown away.<br>
<br>
Dropped loot <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SHOULD</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> become obsolete, but something you devote a year or so to, should not.<br>
<br>
The idea that the Epic pet should always remain king isn't fair to think.. but the idea that the Epic weapon should have lasting impact is a valuable one.<br>
